title: Cleared L0A WA#1 fault by momentarily adjusting water temp PID loop.
text: We were stuck in a catch 22: L0A's temperature was too cold, so the PID loop closed the cooling water mixing valve a lot - so much that there wasn't enough flow to keep the flow switch happy. I briefly lowered the temperature setpoint (circled in image) so that the valve would open and increase the water flow rate. This cleared the flow switch, so that I could turn the modulator on and start putting more heat into the water system. After the station was on for a few seconds, I restored the original setpoint.
